title: Bulk Docs

!! Working on many tiddlers at once

The TiddlyWiki MCP server gives an AI assistant two ''bulk'' tools that operate on multiple tiddlers in one call: `get_tiddlers` (batch read) and `replace_in_tiddlers` (bulk find+replace with dry-run preview). You don't call them yourself. You describe what you want done across N tiddlers, and the AI picks the right tool.

The examples below progress from simple to advanced. Each one shows:

* a realistic ''scenario'' you might run into
* a ''prompt'' you can copy and adapt
* what the AI's ''response'' will look like
* a brief ''behind the scenes'' note pointing at the tool used

